node.title: Stephen Colbert Riffs on Biden’s Order to Release Oil Reserves
node.alt: Stephen Colbert noted that President Biden’s order to release 50 million gallons of oil is “not the best look right after you come back from a climate conference.”
node.description: “For those who don’t know, the strategic reserve is a series of caverns filled with fossil fuel and strategically located inside Rudy Giuliani’s head,” Colbert joked.
node.content: ["Welcome to Best of Late Night, a rundown of the previous night\u2019s highlights that lets you sleep \u2014 and lets us get paid to watch comedy. Here are the 50 best movies on Netflix right now.", "President Biden announced that he would release 50 million barrels of oil from the strategic reserve in an effort to lower gas prices.", "\u201cFor those who don\u2019t know, the strategic reserve is a series of caverns filled with fossil fuel and strategically located inside Rudy Giuliani\u2019s head,\u201d Stephen Colbert joked on Tuesday night.", "Jimmy Kimmel challenged viewers to share the weirdest thing in their mother\u2019s house, inspired by the mom of one of his band members who collects clown figurines.", "Andy Samberg will catch up with his friend Seth Meyers on Wednesday\u2019s \u201cLate Night.\u201d", "Ridley Scott\u2019s \u201cHouse of Gucci\u201d mostly consists of \u201cGuccis yelling at other Guccis.\u201d"]
